{
  "stem": "19210.2",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 247.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They were just anxiously waiting for-- for the words which nobody had at the time for them.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But something else happened in Portugal, too, that I'd like to touch.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "A great number of these immigrants were obviously people that were academicians, doctors, scientists, engineers, professional people, business people, et cetera.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "There was a point in time when if they had the visa, they were allowed to pass through to Portugal, and they were allowed to stay within a given period of time.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I don't know if it was three months or it was six months, but I do remember that after a given period of time, some people would be taken into jail, jailed simply because they were in Portugal illegally.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Their term of staying had elapsed and they couldn't move, so they were taken to jail as prisoners.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And I don't know exactly the details, but I do know that the American Joint Committee-- the Jewish Community of Portugal, the American Joint Committee, the HIAS, the assistant to the Jewish refugees, et cetera, they-- they requested the Portuguese government to allow these people.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "After all, they had suffered enough.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "To be put in jail with common criminals simply because their-- their visa had elapsed wasn't quite justified.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "So there-- there were requests to the Portuguese government to give them some areas where they could stay, wherever, until they would get the visas to-- to leave Portugal so that they would have a dignified stay and dignified life and ease their misery.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So the Portuguese government, I believe, went along with that and they allowed several areas in the neighborhood of Lisbon.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I cannot remember all the names.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was Figuera de Foz I know was one of those and there were several others.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
